{
  "stem": "1316.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And also we, ourselves, children, dressed up in mask and in costumes and went from house to house to get Purim treats.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So this was a very memorable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Also, Passover was memorable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The night of Passover, when we sat at a table.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And my father read the haggadah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he-- he used to read a passage in-- in Hebrew from the book and translate it into Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I used to go-- there were several rabbis, Hasidic rabbis, in the city.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was the [HEBREW] rabbi, the [HEBREW] rabbi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one rabbi of the [HEBREW] was famous all over the world for his compositions, Hasidic compositions which he composed by heart.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't write them down, but they-- Hasidim memorized.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they sang it all over Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was the [HEBREW] rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I used to visit sometimes and see how the-- he conducts his table, how he says Torah, how he-- he divides the-- the [HEBREW], the remnants of the food.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was impressive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Another rabbi was Rabbi [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he was a strange-- he had strange ways.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He-- he gathered to himself simple people-- porters, draymen, so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they followed him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he-- he used to-- to get a slap from him was a privilege.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "To start davening, came in-- which you do in the evening-- he started at midnight.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Was a very beautiful man, a nice man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He lived in a villa.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he-- it was written about him all over Poland because of his outlandish behavior.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and in the school, I remember the first time friends took me to a-- a football match.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were two-- there were two sport clubs, [? you used ?] [? to call it ?] [? that-- ?] sport clubs.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
